
[1]vestry

   VEST'RY, n. [L. vestiarium.]

   1. A room appendant to a church, in which the sacerdotal vestments, in
   which the sacerdotal vestments and sacred utensils are kept, and where
   parochial meetings are held.

   2. A parochial assembly, so called because held in the vestry.

   The council are chosen by the vestry.
